{"author":{"id":"c52cb19fb02c210e51792121b2bae318d19fa8efb308ae796946bf1f79891ad1"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1781516905,"nonce":"yLphQbzB/BK9WUKj4oX/JMemP5E=","title":"Canonicalize index predicates (and CHECK expressions) so publish/status is idempotent","message":"The schema diff compares IndexModel by full equality (diff_named_vec in\ncrates/squealy-model/src/diff.rs), so a desired partial-index predicate never\nmatches the form Postgres introspection returns.\n\nThe Table-derive renders a typed `where = ...` predicate to\n`(\"deleted_at\" IS NULL)` (quoted identifiers; see render_ddl_predicate in\ncrates/squealy/src/expr.rs). The Postgres introspector reads live predicates via\n`pg_get_expr(i.indpred, i.indrelid)` (crates/squealy-postgresql/src/introspect.rs),\nwhich deparses to `(deleted_at IS NULL)` — unquoted lowercase identifiers, and for\nvalue literals an added type cast (e.g. `(label = 'x'::text)`).\n\nEffect: after a clean publish of a typed partial unique index, the next\nstatus/publish keeps planning a spurious AlterIndex, so the operation is not\nidempotent.\n\nThis is the same deparse-canonicalization class as free-form SQL expressions\nelsewhere. CheckModel.expression has the identical gap today: the user writes\n`check = \"age \u003e 0\"`, introspection returns `(age \u003e 0)`, and there is no\ncanonicalization of the desired side (check_expression only strips the\n`CHECK (...)` wrapper). So this should be solved generally, not just for indexes.\n\nPaths NOT involving live introspection are already correct/idempotent:\nrender_create (create-from-scratch), package export/import (both sides use the\nrendered form), and query-side DDL.\n\nProposed approach:\n- Add a canonicalization hook on SchemaIntrospect, e.g.\n  `canonical_index_predicate(\u0026self, \u0026str) -\u003e String` (default identity), applied\n  in canonicalize_model alongside canonical_sql_type / canonical_identity_mode.\n- Postgres implements it to normalize the desired predicate to its pg_get_expr\n  deparse form: unquote safe lowercase identifiers (quote only when pg would),\n  and add literal type casts to match.\n- Generalize the same pass to CheckModel.expression so checks become idempotent\n  too.\n- Tests: round-trip a typed partial index through canonicalize -\u003e diff and assert\n  no AlterIndex; same for a CHECK expression.\n\nContext: follow-up from PR #25 (partial / filtered unique indexes), review thread\nhttps://github.com/smohekey/squealy/pull/25#discussion_r3412195976","files":null}]}